  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/" }
})} />

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring PH words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "NYMPH (15 pts), GLYPH (14 pts), SPHINX (18 pts), and PHOSPHOR (18 pts) rank among top PH words. The P(3) + H(4) combination provides a strong 7-point base." }},
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does PH always make an /f/ sound in Scrabble words?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Almost always. PH makes an /f/ sound in words of Greek origin like PHONE, PHOTO, and GRAPH. Rare exceptions exist in compound words where P and H are in different syllables (UPHILL)." }},
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What short PH words are valid in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "PHO (8 pts) is the shortest common PH word — it's a Vietnamese soup. PHI (8 pts, the Greek letter) and PHT (not valid) are often confused. GRAPH (11 pts) and MORPH (12 pts) are solid short plays." }}
  ]
})} />

