<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Containing PH — Scrabble /f/ Sound Digraph</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">PH is the Greek-origin digraph that sounds like /f/ — and it's a Scrabble scoring machine. P contributes 3 points and H adds 4, giving every PH word a 7-point head start. Words like NYMPH, GLYPH, and PHANTOM combine this digraph with other consonants for devastating scores.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why PH Scores Big</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">P(3) + H(4) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">200+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid PH words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Greek</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Origin language</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>PH and CH share the same 7-point base value, but PH words tend to include other high-value consonants (Y, G, X) more frequently due to their Greek etymology. This pushes average PH word scores higher than most digraphs.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring PH Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
