<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy for PH Words</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-GRAPH builds outward:</span> GRAPH → GRAPHS, GRAPHIC, GEOGRAPHY. Start with the base word and extend it on later turns for compound scoring.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PH words resist hooks:</span> NYMPH and GLYPH end in consonant clusters that are very hard to extend. Use them defensively to limit opponent options.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target H on DLS/TLS:</span> H is worth 4 points. On a Double Letter it becomes 8, on a Triple it becomes 12. Always check premium alignment for the H tile.</p>
